Act III, sc. 2, adds Gupes to the company of the preceding one. He comes forth having his neck twisted and is also dressed like Torcol. He talks Portuguese with his servant, Trico; and these two so thoroughly deceive Dulman, that he delivers over to them the money, the contract and the secret sign, whereby Torcol was to know the true servant of Ignoramus They treat Dul- man plentifully to wine, and Cupes implores him to have an oversight, that Rosabella-Polla shall be well treated at the hands of his master.
